720942f-a.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 29th Street (East)
720942f-a.text:
Lexington Avenue, north from East 29th Street. Cn
the left, at 30th Street appears the First Moravian Church
(founded 1746) and the N. Y. School of Design for Women.

711919f-a.title: Manhattan: 29th Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
711919f-a.text:
131 to 135 East 29th Street (left to right), adioining and east
of the N.E. corner of Lexington Ave., showing the Congregation
Adereth El at No. 135. The adjoining structure No. 133 is used in
conjunction with same and is the Talmud Torah Adereth El. No. 131,
which appears on the left is occupied by the International Federation
of Catholic Alumnae, Business and Bulletin Headquarters.
September 1937.
George D. Chinn.
